Dormakaba is now defending a patent infringement suit filed by Liberty Access Technologies Licensing LLC in the Eastern District of Texas, one of the most plaintiff-favorable venues in the country. NPE plaintiffs operating in that district tend to press hard early, and without an assigned judge yet, the schedule could move quickly once one is named.

Stilta works with in-house IP teams to accelerate exactly the work that matters most at this stage: prior-art searches against the asserted patents, claim-chart analysis, and a clear-eyed read on IPR or PTAB petition viability. Getting that picture early shapes every decision that follows, from claim construction positioning to settlement leverage.

If it would be useful, we are happy to send a brief overview of how Stilta approaches NPE defense work in E.D. Tex. cases. Just reply here and we can get that to you quickly.

